title: GDG DevFest Florida 2016
motto: Be a GDG. Be a Hero!
subscribe-note: No spam, only the latest news and updates!
tickets-details: Tickets grant access to all speaker sessions, breakouts, code labs, coffee breaks, lunch, and entrance to the after party. Accommodation and/or travel is NOT included in the ticket price.
run-out-tickets: We have run out all our tickets
team-page-text: Google is known all around the world. Everyone is 'googling', checking on 'maps' and communicating in 'gmail'. For simple users, they are services that just work, but not for us. Developers see much more: APIs, scalability issues, complex technology stacks. Approaching that technology with an open, accessible community is what GDG is about.
description: DevFest Florida is the first combined DevFest being organized by three Google Developer Groups in the central Florida area: Space Coast, Central Florida, and Sun Coast. These GDG chapters support the Orlando, Tampa, and Melbourne areas of central Florida. It will be the largest Google-tech conference in Florida in 2016!

location-description: Immerse yourself in the sophisticated and functional environment in our recently renovated Orlando meeting spaces. From intimate to extravagant, casual to elegant, our versatile spaces accommodate up to 800 guests.
about-organizers: GDG Sun Coast, GDG Space Coast, and GDG Central Florida with support from multiple GDG members from across Florida are proud the be organizing DevFest Florida.
about-gdg: Google Developers Group (GDG) - is an open, volunteer, tech community that creates exciting content and shares experiences about Google technologies.
